Liverpool ace, Sadio Mane has been included in the 2019 UEFA Champions League Team of the Year. UEFA released the Champions League team in a post on their official website on Wednesday. Mane was included in the team after his impressive performance in 2019 for both club and country. The Senegalese forward made the list, alongside Barcelona captain, Lionel Messi and Juventus forward, Cristiano Ronaldo. 2019 UEFA Champions League Team of the Year: Alisson Becker Trent Alexander-Arnold Matthijs de Ligt Virgil va Dijk Andy Robertson Frenkie de Jong Kevin De Bruyne Lionel Messi Cristiano Ronaldo Robert Lewandowski Sadio Mane